import pandas as pd

df_sales = pd.DataFrame({
    "store": ["A"]*7 + ["B"]*7,
    "day": list(range(1,8))*2,
    "sales": [10,12,15,14,13,11,9, 8,9,10,12,15,18,20],
    "stock": [100,88,73,59,46,35,26, 120,112,102,90,75,57,37]
})

display(df_sales)

# ÌíÄÏù¥

```python
df_sales['ma3_sales'] = df_sales.groupby('store')['sales'].transform(lambda s: s.rolling(3, min_periods=1).mean())
display(df_sales)
df_sales['days_left'] = df_sales['stock']/df_sales['ma3_sales']
df_sales['is_risk'] = df_sales['days_left']<=3
display(df_sales)
df_sales_sorted = df_sales.sort_values(by=['store', 'day'])
store_feat = df_sales_sorted.groupby('store').agg(
    last_stock=('stock','last'),
    last_ma3=('ma3_sales','last'),
    last_days_left=('days_left','last'),
    risk_days=('is_risk','sum')
).reset_index()
display(store_feat)
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
fig1, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=2, ncols=1, figsize=(7,6))
stores = ['A', 'B']
for idx, store in enumerate(stores):
    r = df_sales[df_sales['store']==store]
    r_scatter=df_sales[(df_sales['store']==store)&(df_sales['is_risk'])]
    axes[idx].plot(r['day'], r['stock'])
    axes[idx].scatter(r_scatter['day'], r_scatter['stock'], color='red')
    axes[idx].twinx().plot(r['day'], r['days_left'], color = 'blue', linestyle='--')
    axes[idx].set_title(f'Store {store} Inventory Risk')
    axes[idx].grid(False)
fig2, ax2 = plt.subplots(figsize=(7,4))
ax2.bar(store_feat['store'], store_feat['last_days_left'])
ax2.axhline(3, linestyle='--',color='gray')
ax2.set_title("Final Inventory Coverage (Days)")
ax2.grid(False)
plt.show()
```
